00:19:51.670 --> 00:19:54.080
&gt;&gt; Sanford Levinson: And so,
why do we have that legislation?

00:19:54.080 --> 00:19:59.450
The answer is not really
the House of Representatives

00:19:59.450 --> 00:20:01.650
where representation
is presentable.

00:20:01.650 --> 00:20:07.920
So, California has, I think,
54 members of Congress.

00:20:07.920 --> 00:20:10.170
We're from Texas
most of the year,

00:20:10.170 --> 00:20:13.650
Texas has 36 members
of the House.

00:20:13.650 --> 00:20:19.790
So, where small states
have small numbers

00:20:19.790 --> 00:20:23.770
of representatives, there
are 7 states that have fewer

00:20:23.770 --> 00:20:26.820
that have more senators
than representatives,

00:20:26.820 --> 00:20:29.410
that is they have
one representative,

00:20:29.410 --> 00:20:32.300
the minimum number, but
they have two senators,

00:20:32.300 --> 00:20:35.210
because the Constitution says
each state gets two senators.

00:20:35.210 --> 00:20:38.950
So, you really have to
look at the Senate in order

00:20:38.950 --> 00:20:43.040
to understand a lot of
agricultural policy.

00:20:43.040 --> 00:20:49.290
There, it turns out that the
small population states also

00:20:49.290 --> 00:20:54.760
tend to be more rural than
the large population states.

00:20:54.760 --> 00:20:58.980
Texas has tons of
acreage but we also have 4

00:20:58.980 --> 00:21:01.400
of the 11 largest
cities in the country.

00:21:01.400 --> 00:21:04.980
We're the most, we're the
densest state in the country,

00:21:04.980 --> 00:21:07.770
which most people don't
realize that Texas is full

00:21:07.770 --> 00:21:11.530
of Ranches and things like that.

00:21:11.530 --> 00:21:15.720
But, the senators from the
upper Midwest, in particular,

00:21:15.720 --> 00:21:20.590
have lots of power in the Senate

00:21:20.590 --> 00:21:26.370
because of the each states gets
two senators rule and also,

00:21:26.370 --> 00:21:30.090
the nature of bicameralism
that we talk about.

00:21:30.090 --> 00:21:31.440
Pardon? Yep.

00:21:31.440 --> 00:21:34.980
That there are two houses
of Congress not one.

00:21:34.980 --> 00:21:39.560
And, for a bill to become a
law, both houses have to agree,

00:21:39.560 --> 00:21:43.230
every dotted I every
crossed T. Now, the Senate

00:21:43.230 --> 00:21:45.630
and the House are very
different, precisely,

00:21:45.630 --> 00:21:48.900
because House is
proportional, Senate is not.

00:21:48.900 --> 00:21:50.340
How'd that come about?

00:21:50.340 --> 00:21:55.470
It came about because of what
is often called the Great

00:21:55.470 --> 00:21:57.580
Compromise, capital
G, capital C,

00:21:57.580 --> 00:22:03.660
where the small states basically
said we're going to walk

00:22:03.660 --> 00:22:08.560
out if you don't give us equal
representation in the Senate.

00:22:08.560 --> 00:22:11.870
James Madison, so called
Father of the Constitution,

00:22:11.870 --> 00:22:14.110
thought this was
a terrible idea.

00:22:14.110 --> 00:22:18.090
He never, ever had
a good word to say

00:22:18.090 --> 00:22:22.020
about equal voting
power in the Senate.

00:22:22.020 --> 00:22:24.710
But, he did, ultimately,
agree to accept it

00:22:24.710 --> 00:22:27.360
because the alternative
would be no constitution.

00:22:27.360 --> 00:22:32.120
Let me point out that another
very, very important compromise

00:22:32.120 --> 00:22:37.480
that people never refer to
as a capital G capital C,

00:22:37.480 --> 00:22:41.010
Great Compromise,
was the one saying

00:22:41.010 --> 00:22:46.260
that slaves would be
counted as 3/5ths of person

00:22:46.260 --> 00:22:51.150
for computing the
voting power of states.

00:22:51.150 --> 00:22:56.090
And, this meant that slave
states got extra representation

00:22:56.090 --> 00:22:58.280
in the House of Representatives

00:22:58.280 --> 00:23:02.690
because their slaves were
counted as if they were really

00:23:02.690 --> 00:23:08.420
and truly being represented,
which of course they weren't.

00:23:08.420 --> 00:23:11.330
But, they did help give
additional voting power

00:23:11.330 --> 00:23:12.870
to Virginia.

00:23:12.870 --> 00:23:16.730
And, that doe help to explain
why Thomas Jefferson instead

00:23:16.730 --> 00:23:21.220
of John Adams was
elected president in 1800.

00:23:21.220 --> 00:23:24.610
Both of these compromises
were central

00:23:24.610 --> 00:23:27.010
to having a Constitution at all.

00:23:27.010 --> 00:23:30.400
One of them, as I say, is often
called the Great Compromise,

00:23:30.400 --> 00:23:31.700
the other isn't.

00:23:31.700 --> 00:23:34.950
But, what's really important
is that people didn't end

00:23:34.950 --> 00:23:39.170
up agreeing, you know,
it's really a fined idea

00:23:39.170 --> 00:23:41.210
that Delaware should
have the same number

00:23:41.210 --> 00:23:43.350
of senators as Virginia.

00:23:43.350 --> 00:23:46.530
James Madison never agreed
that that was a fine idea, but,

00:23:46.530 --> 00:23:50.790
it was a price that had to be
paid, similarly with regard

00:23:50.790 --> 00:23:54.050
to the compromises over slavery.

00:23:54.050 --> 00:23:57.830
We live with both of
those compromises today

00:23:57.830 --> 00:24:01.040
in quite different ways.

00:24:01.040 --> 00:24:03.890
But, with the Senate,
in particular,

00:24:03.890 --> 00:24:06.550
we live with the compromise

00:24:06.550 --> 00:24:12.960
in that the small states
have what we regard

00:24:12.960 --> 00:24:17.110
as excessive voting
power in the Senate.

00:24:17.110 --> 00:24:20.420
And, the voting power
is translated to things

00:24:20.420 --> 00:24:25.250
like agricultural
bills or subsidies,

00:24:25.250 --> 00:24:28.310
protection for coal production.

00:24:28.310 --> 00:24:31.280
Because, not only are
the states small, but,

00:24:31.280 --> 00:24:33.820
it turns out that senators

00:24:33.820 --> 00:24:39.230
from small states
represent fewer interests.

00:24:39.230 --> 00:24:44.130
If, in fact, the small states
were really and truly as diverse

00:24:44.130 --> 00:24:47.200
as the large states, like Texas,

00:24:47.200 --> 00:24:49.270
then frankly it might
not matter.

00:24:49.270 --> 00:24:53.960
But, small states tend to
be far, far less diverse

00:24:53.960 --> 00:25:00.430
in ever measure of diversity
whether it's the economic base,

00:25:00.430 --> 00:25:04.460
the tomography of the
population, small states tend

00:25:04.460 --> 00:25:09.510
to be whiter than Texas.

00:25:09.510 --> 00:25:13.400
We have the most diversity in
the country is Houston Texas.

00:25:13.400 --> 00:25:22.300
And, this has real implications
for why bills become law

00:25:22.300 --> 00:25:28.240
or why a lot of bills never
stand a chance of becoming law.

